'''科雷馬公路'''（{{lang-ru|Колымская трасса}}），正式名稱是'''R504聯邦公路科雷馬段'''（{{lang|ru|Федеральная автомобильная дорога «Колыма»}}），是[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]的一條幹線公路，同時也是[[科雷馬|科雷馬]]地區唯一的公路，連接[[馬加丹|馬加丹]]和[[下別斯佳赫|下別斯佳赫]]{{notetag|道路終於[[勒拿河|勒拿河]]東岸，可藉冬季冰封的河面和夏季渡輪前往[[雅庫茨克|雅庫茨克]]}}，全長2,032公里，於下別斯佳赫接續[[勒拿公路|勒拿公路]]。

== 路線 ==
科雷馬公路是俄羅斯[[遠東聯邦管區|遠東地區]]現時主要的高速公路之一。連接[[雅庫特|雅庫特]]和[[馬加丹|馬加丹]]地區，是[[薩哈（雅庫特）共和國|薩哈（雅庫特）共和國]]東部、馬加丹地區西部和中部唯一的核心道路，並提供通往太平洋沿岸的通道。

這條路始於下別斯佳赫，毗鄰[[勒拿公路|勒拿公路]]，途經[[漢德加|漢德加]]、[[烏斯季涅拉|烏斯季涅拉]]、[[阿爾特克_(薩哈共和國)|阿爾特克]]、[[卡德克昌|卡德克昌]]、[[蘇蘇曼|蘇蘇曼]]、[[亞戈德諾耶_(馬加丹州)|亞戈德諾耶]]等城鎮，結束於馬加丹。科雷馬高速公路途中有一處分岔點，分為南線和北線，南線主要位在雅庫特境內（{{le|丘別梅|Kyubeme}} - {{le|托姆托爾|Tomtor, Oymyakonsky District, Sakha Republic}}  - {{le|庫拉納赫薩拉|Kuranakh-Sala}}  - [[卡德克昌|卡德克昌]]），路途較北線短，是歷史悠久道路，建造時間比現有道路要早得多，但在1970年代後已逐漸被遺棄。<ref name="news">{{cite news |title=Man frozen to death after Google Maps wrong turn |url=https://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/real-life/news-life/man-frozen-to-death-after-google-maps-wrong-turn/news-story/13e10cbbc96494ee26e6dea29f4fb469 |accessdate=2022-03-12 |work=News.com.au |date=2020-12-11 |language=en |archive-date=2022-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220423025506/https://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/real-life/news-life/man-frozen-to-death-after-google-maps-wrong-turn/news-story/13e10cbbc96494ee26e6dea29f4fb469 }}</ref>北線為現行主要道路，位於馬加丹地區境內（[[帕拉特卡_(马加丹州)|帕拉特卡]] - [[烏斯季奧姆丘格|烏斯季奧姆丘格]] - [[布爾什維克_(馬加丹州)|布爾什維克]]）。

==歷史 ==

[[File:Kolyma_road00.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Kolyma_road01.jpg|thumb]]
隨著1920年代採礦業的發展，[[蘇聯|蘇聯]]在[[雅庫特|雅庫特]]和科雷馬開始建立地方道路網絡。1931年11月，{{Le|遠北建築信託|Dalstroy}}成立，其中一項任務便是使用囚犯建設科雷馬公路。

該公路始建於1932年，並於1953年落成。興建時動用了大量的[[古拉格|古拉格]]政治犯興建，因氣候嚴寒，導致死傷無數，故又被稱為'''屍骨之路'''（{{lang|ru|дорога на костях}}）。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/russia/1404085/Road-of-Bones-where-slaves-perished.html |title='Road of Bones' where slaves perished |first=Marcus |last=Warren |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |date=2002-08-10 |publisher=[[Telegraph_Media_Group|TMG]] |location=[[London,_UK|London]] |issn=0307-1235 |oclc=49632006 |accessdate=2012-02-05 |archive-date=2011-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110206103913/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/russia/1404085/Road-of-Bones-where-slaves-perished.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.russianlife.com/archive/article/params/Number/1186/ |title=Road of Bones to the Coldest Place in the World – |first=Gary & Monica |last=Westcott |work=Russian Life |year=2012 |accessdate=2012-02-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313114900/http://www.russianlife.com/archive/article/params/Number/1186/ |archive-date=2012-03-13 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Федеральная автодорога Р504 «Колыма» |url=http://strana.ru/places/198331/info |website=Страна.ру |accessdate=2020-03-11 |archive-date=2019-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190616225435/http://strana.ru/places/198331/info |dead-url=no }}</ref>

這條道路是古拉格中最寒冷、死亡率最高以及最遙遠的勞改營。<ref name="nyt">{{cite news |last1=Higgins |first1=Andrew |title=Along Russia’s ‘Road of Bones,’ Relics of Suffering and Despair |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/22/world/europe/russia-stalin-gulag-kolyma-magadan.html |accessdate=2022-03-12 |work=The New York Times |date=2020-11-22 |language=en |archive-date=2022-04-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220426024829/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/22/world/europe/russia-stalin-gulag-kolyma-magadan.html }}</ref>據各種估計，在道路建設期間，約有25萬至100萬人死亡。<ref>Hochschild, Adam (2003) [1994]. «17: Beyond the Pole Star». The Unquiet Ghost: Russians Remember Stalin. Boston: Houghton Mifflin Harcourt. p. 237. {{ISBN|9780547524979}}. Retrieved 14 June 2017. «Secret police authorities in Kolyma today say there are records — sometimes a complete file, sometime just a name on a list — of two million men and women who were shipped to the territory between 1930 and the mid-1950s. But no one knows, even approximately, how many of these prisoners died. Even historians who have spent years studying Kolyma come up with radically different numbers. I asked four such researchers, who between them have written or edited more than half a dozen books on the gulag, what was the total Kolyma death toll. One estimated it at 250,000, another at 300,000, one at 800,000, and one at 'more than 1,000,000.'»</ref>而許多人被葬於道路一旁或直接埋在道路下方。<ref>Thompson G., (2002) ''Kolyma — The Road of Death''</ref>

===事故===
2020年，兩名俄羅斯年輕男子使用[[Google地圖|Google地圖]]導航，誤入舊路線（即南線），隨後汽車於{{le|托姆托爾|Tomtor, Oymyakonsky District, Sakha Republic}}大概100公里外的廢棄村莊{{le|庫拉納赫-薩拉|Kuranakh-Sala}}附近，在約-50°C的環境下拋錨，其中一人被凍死，而另一人則四肢被[[凍傷|凍傷]]。<ref name="news"/><ref>{{cite news |author1=李納德 |title=18歲俄男信Google Maps導航受困「屍骨之路」 負50度變冰柱慘死 {{!}} 聯合新聞網 |url=https://udn.com/news/story/7168/5094950 |accessdate=2022-06-18 |work=聯合報 |date=20201216T165532Z}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Дорога костей |url=https://holod.media/2021/06/23/doroga-kostey/ |accessdate=2022-06-18 |work=Журнал «Холод» |date=2021-06-23 |language=ru}}</ref>
